<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920310-0041</DOCNO><DOCID>920310-0041.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Niagara Share Corp.:   Firm Agrees to Be Acquired   For Scudder Growth Shares</HL><DATE>03/10/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   NGS</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES (FIS)MUTUAL AND MONEY-MARKET FUNDS (FND)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>MUTUAL FUNDS (FND)ACQUISITIONS, MERGERS, TAKEOVERS (TNM)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Investment manager Scudder, Stevens andamp; Clark Inc., Boston,said it signed a letter of intent to acquire substantiallyall the assets of Niagara Share Corp., New York, aliquidating closed-end fund, for shares of the Scudder Growthand Income Fund of equal net asset value.   The proposal is subject to a definitive agreement,approval by Niagara Share shareholders and by trustees of theScudder fund. Scudder Growth, with assets of $743 million,invests in larger, more well-established, dividend payingcompanies.</LP><TEXT>   Robert J.A. Irwin, president of Niagara Share, said thefund has about $220 million in assets, about 50% in cash anda net asset value of just over $15 a share. The fund hasslightly more than 14 million shares outstanding. &quot;A fund oursize is just too small,&quot; Mr. Irwin said. &quot;It is hard for aclosed-end fund to bring in new money.&quot;   Following the share exchange, Niagara Share would make aliquidating distribution of Scudder Growth and Income Fundshares to its shareholders in exchange for their NiagaraShare common stock.   Niagara Share officials said shareholders should benefitover the long term from the lower expense ratio of theScudder fund.   In New York Stock Exchange trading, Niagara Share stockclosed at $14.625 a share, up 12.5 cents.</TEXT></DOC>